cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CR

The paper discusses bibliometric indicators and methodologies for evaluating research performance, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with bibliometrics and evaluation of research. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also relevant as it discusses the impact of evaluation on individuals and institutions. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as it deals with measuring the impact of research publications. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as it discusses the evaluation of research performance in the context of social networks. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is relevant as it discusses the risks and limitations of evaluation practices, which are relevant to the security and privacy of individuals and institutions.
